title: No Man's Land
overview: Bosnia and Herzegovina during 1993 at the time of the heaviest fighting between the two warring sides. Two soldiers from opposing sides in the conflict, Nino and Ciki, become trapped in no man's land, whilst a third soldier becomes a living booby trap.

title: Jojo Rabbit
overview: A young boy in Hitler's army finds out his mother is hiding a Jewish girl in their home.

title: Chhichhore
overview: A tragic incident forces Anirudh, a middle-aged man, to take a trip down memory lane and reminisce his college days along with his friends, who were labelled as losers.

title: Naked
overview: Parallel tales of two sexually obsessed men, one hurting and annoying women physically and mentally, one wandering around the city talking to strangers and experiencing dimensions of life.

title: Stalag 17
overview: When two escaping American World War II prisoners are killed, the German P.O.W. camp barracks black marketeer, J.J. Sefton, is suspected of being an informer.

title: Druk
overview: Four friends, all high school teachers, test a theory that they will improve their lives by maintaining a constant level of alcohol in their blood.

title: Happiness
overview: The lives of several individuals intertwine as they go about their lives in their own unique ways, engaging in acts society as a whole might find disturbing in a desperate search for human connection.

title: Rushmore
overview: The extracurricular king of Rushmore Preparatory School is put on academic probation.

title: The Great Dictator
overview: Dictator Adenoid Hynkel tries to expand his empire while a poor Jewish barber tries to avoid persecution from Hynkel's regime.

title: Amarcord
overview: A series of comedic and nostalgic vignettes set in a 1930s Italian coastal town.

title: Vizontele
overview: Lives of residents in a small Anatolian village change when television is introduced to them

title: Perfetti sconosciuti
overview: Seven long-time friends get together for a dinner. When they decide to share with each other the content of every text message, email and phone call they receive, many secrets start to unveil and the equilibrium trembles.

title: Adaptation.
overview: A lovelorn screenwriter becomes desperate as he tries and fails to adapt 'The Orchid Thief' by Susan Orlean for the screen.

title: La règle du jeu
overview: A bourgeois life in France at the onset of World War II, as the rich and their poor servants meet up at a French chateau.

title: Yeopgijeogin geunyeo
overview: A young man sees a drunk, cute woman standing too close to the tracks at a metro station in Seoul and pulls her back. She ends up getting him into trouble repeatedly after that, starting on the train.

title: Patton
overview: The World War II phase of the career of controversial American general George S. Patton.

title: Uri: The Surgical Strike
overview: Indian army special forces execute a covert operation, avenging the killing of fellow army men at their base by a terrorist group.

title: C.R.A.Z.Y.
overview: A young French-Canadian, growing up in the 1960s and 1970s, struggles to reconcile his emerging homosexuality with his father's conservative values and his own Catholic beliefs.

title: Relatos salvajes
overview: Six short stories that explore the extremities of human behavior involving people in distress.

title: Do the Right Thing
overview: On the hottest day of the year on a street in the Bedford-Stuyvesant section of Brooklyn, everyone's hate and bigotry smolders and builds until it explodes into violence.
